'''Kotohira Shrine''' (金刀比羅神社) is a {{ill|Shinto|ja|神道|qq=draft}} shrine located in {{ill|Kuji|ja|久慈市|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|ja|岩手県|qq=draft}}, in Minatomachi. It is affectionately known as "Konpira-san."

The shrine is situated on elevated ground, overlooking {{ill|Kuji Bay|ja|久慈湾|qq=draft}}. It also serves as a designated {{ill|Tsunami evacuation facility|ja|津波避難施設|qq=draft}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bousai.city.kuji.iwate.jp/contents/pc/pdf/hazardmap/jishintsunami/07.pdf |format=PDF |title=Tsunami Hazard Map |publisher=Kuji City |accessdate=October 28, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304213804/http://bousai.city.kuji.iwate.jp/contents/pc/pdf/hazardmap/jishintsunami/07.pdf |archive-date=March 4, 2016}}</ref>. During the {{ill|Great East Japan Earthquake|ja|東日本大震災|qq=draft}} on March 11, 2011, many people sought refuge at the shrine.

