金刀比羅神社_(久慈市)
{{Unreferenced clearly|date=April 3, 2013}} {{Infobox religious building| religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | name = Kotohira Shrine (金刀比羅神社) | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] |image = [[File:Kuji-konpira.jpg|thumb|Sanctuary]] | location = Minatomachi 13-90, {{ill|Kuji|ja|久慈市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuji|qq=}}, {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|ja|岩手県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iwate Prefecture|qq=}} | Latitude degree = 40 | Latitude minute = 12 | Latitude second = 11.5 | Longitude degree = 141 | Longitude minute = 47 | Longitude second = 28.7 | deity = {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大物主命|1=Ōmononushi|lt=Ōmononushi-no-Mikoto|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuninushi|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmononushi|qq=}} ([[Konpira Gongen]]) | Sacred object = | Classification = | Established = 1718 | MainHall = | Alternatename = | Pilgrimage = | AnnualFestival = August 10 | Rituals = }}
'''Kotohira Shrine''' (金刀比羅神社) is a {{ill|Shinto|ja|神道|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto|qq=}} shrine located in {{ill|Kuji|ja|久慈市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuji|qq=}}, {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|ja|岩手県|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iwate Prefecture|qq=}}, in Minatomachi. It is affectionately known as "Konpira-san."
The shrine is situated on elevated ground, overlooking {{ill|Kuji Bay|ja|久慈湾|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuji Bay|qq=}}. It also serves as a designated {{ill|Tsunami evacuation facility|ja|津波避難施設|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsunami evacuation facility|qq=}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bousai.city.kuji.iwate.jp/contents/pc/pdf/hazardmap/jishintsunami/07.pdf |format=PDF |title=Tsunami Hazard Map |publisher=Kuji City |accessdate=October 28, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304213804/http://bousai.city.kuji.iwate.jp/contents/pc/pdf/hazardmap/jishintsunami/07.pdf |archive-date=March 4, 2016}}</ref>. During the {{ill|Great East Japan Earthquake|ja|東日本大震災|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Great East Japan Earthquake|qq=}} on March 11, 2011, many people sought refuge at the shrine.
