'''Kotohira Shrine''' (金刀比羅神社) is a [[:en:Shinto|Shinto]] shrine located in [[:en:Kuji, Iwate|Kuji]], [[:en:Iwate Prefecture|Iwate Prefecture]], in Minatomachi. It is affectionately known as "Konpira-san."
The shrine is situated on elevated ground, overlooking {{ill|Kuji Bay|ja|久慈湾|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuji Bay|qq=}}. It also serves as a designated {{ill|Tsunami evacuation facility|ja|津波避難施設|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsunami evacuation facility|qq=}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bousai.city.kuji.iwate.jp/contents/pc/pdf/hazardmap/jishintsunami/07.pdf |format=PDF |title=Tsunami Hazard Map |publisher=Kuji City |accessdate=October 28, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304213804/http://bousai.city.kuji.iwate.jp/contents/pc/pdf/hazardmap/jishintsunami/07.pdf |archive-date=March 4, 2016}}</ref>. During the [[:en:Aftermath of the 2011 Tōhoku earthquake and tsunami|Great East Japan Earthquake]] on March 11, 2011, many people sought refuge at the shrine.
