'''Kotohira Shrine''' (金刀比羅神社) is a {{ill|Shinto|en|Shinto|qid=Q812767|lt=Shinto|1=Shinto}} shrine located in {{ill|Kuji, Iwate|en|Kuji, Iwate|qid=Q695911|lt=Kuji|1=Kuji, Iwate}}, {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|en|Iwate Prefecture|qid=Q48326|lt=Iwate Prefecture|1=Iwate Prefecture}}, in Minatomachi. It is affectionately known as "Konpira-san."

The shrine is situated on elevated ground, overlooking {{ill|Kuji Bay|ja|久慈湾|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kuji Bay|1=Kuji Bay|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11369340}}. It also serves as a designated {{ill|Tsunami evacuation facility|ja|津波避難施設|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsunami evacuation facility|1=tsunami evacuation facility|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q17177367}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bousai.city.kuji.iwate.jp/contents/pc/pdf/hazardmap/jishintsunami/07.pdf |format=PDF |title=Tsunami Hazard Map |publisher=Kuji City |accessdate=October 28, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304213804/http://bousai.city.kuji.iwate.jp/contents/pc/pdf/hazardmap/jishintsunami/07.pdf |archive-date=March 4, 2016}}</ref>. During the {{ill|Aftermath of the 2011 Tōhoku earthquake and tsunami|en|Aftermath of the 2011 Tōhoku earthquake and tsunami|qid=Q1136168|lt=Great East Japan Earthquake|1=Aftermath of the 2011 Tōhoku earthquake and tsunami}} on March 11, 2011, many people sought refuge at the shrine.

